                                "reference": "INSPIRATION",
                                "subject": "Inspiration"
                            },
                            "text": "In the Hindu religion, Kali is the goddess of preservation, transformation and destruction. Her name comes from the word \"kālá\" (time), and she represents the destructive power of time. She is the dark counterpart of Shiva. But Kali also has a benevolent role: She destroys evil spirits and provides protection for devout believers."
                        },
